<subSubSection id="1EF421CCFFB7C115FF67DF5EFE547ADD" lastPageId="47" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="56517247FFB7C117FF67DF5EFD437ADD" blockId="45.[151,1436,259,430]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB7C117FF67DF5EFEE47A49" bold="true" box="[151,274,259,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from others in the genus by the crown length 0.8x or less than interocular width, the stout and symmetrical form of the aedeagus, aedeagus with a short unpaired apical process, paired apical processes of aedeagus short and triangular, and phragma sides in caudal view lying laterad of anal tube, separated from each other, and broadly rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56517247FFB7C117FF37DFCEFD8D7AFA" blockId="45.[151,1436,259,430]" box="[199,635,403,430]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB7C117FF37DFCEFEFD7AF9" bold="true" box="[199,267,403,429]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Body.</emphasis>
Male, 
<quantity id="9116DFA2FFB7C117FEA9DFCEFE597AFA" box="[345,431,403,430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
to forewing apex.
</paragraph>
